msgid "How to Use the Calculator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:3
# 1f0aaeba21d94c2ea4698725e86d62d4
msgid "The calculator has a total of six editable text boxes, where four can be used to input values (odds and stakes) and the other two to insert parameters (commission and bias)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:7
# b27306d1a2194e1a97b549b46f6c851e
msgid "The keyboard configuration implemented (see :ref:`navigation` and :ref:`clearing`), allows the user to efficiently insert values with a *desktop keyboard* by placing his two hands in the following way: the left hand can be placed on the left side with the index finger on the *TAB* key and the thumb alternating between the *SPACE* and *SHIFT* keys; the right hand can be used to press the numeric pad and arrows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:22
# 25f705d364e347b593809e05d00914d3
msgid "Navigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:23
# be1c20aedeff4497a348b048411d5217
msgid "Navigation between text boxes is made with the *TAB* and *ENTER* keys. *SHIFT* reverses the orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:26
# 11a11aa110aa4d5c9a6afdb14ebb00f2
msgid "The order of the text boxes was defined based on the following assumption: when a trader is observing a market, he is first focused on the odds, and posteriorly on the stakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial.rst:33
# 87215d92575549769e1e7d1e38d3f4f5
msgid "In order to navigate in the opposite direction, just hold the *SHIFT* key while pressing *TAB* or *ENTER*."
msgstr ""

